@ApiService_HostAddress = http://localhost:5410

### The static key StaffAuthFilter checks on every staff endpoint below. The value here matches the
### PLACEHOLDER-... default in appsettings.json — a real deployment overrides that setting via user-secrets or
### an environment variable, and this variable would need to match whatever it's changed to.
@staffKey = PLACEHOLDER-staff-key-never-a-real-secret-see-CLAUDE.md

### Current queue state + latest sequence number. Seeded with "Jane Test" (A-042) and "Sam Sample" (A-043)
### on first run against a fresh database. Public, hardened by CORS only (no write, no token needed).
GET {{ApiService_HostAddress}}/queue
Accept: application/json

###

### Fetch a fresh check-in token (short-lived, HMAC-signed — see CheckInTokenService). Copy the "token" value
### from the response into @checkInToken below before running POST /checkin; a stale or missing token gets
### 401 ProblemDetails from CheckInTokenFilter.
GET {{ApiService_HostAddress}}/checkin/token
Accept: application/json

###

### Check in a new visitor. Server assigns the id, position, and sequence number. Requires a fresh token from
### GET /checkin/token above, echoed on X-CheckIn-Token — omitting it, or sending an expired one, returns 401.
@checkInToken = replace-with-a-token-from-get-checkin-token
POST {{ApiService_HostAddress}}/checkin
Content-Type: application/json
X-CheckIn-Token: {{checkInToken}}

{
  "displayName": "Sam Sample Two",
  "ticketNumber": "A-044"
}

###

### Call the oldest Waiting entry to Serving. Returns 409 Conflict if nobody is Waiting. Staff-only: requires
### X-Staff-Key; omitting it or sending the wrong value returns 401 ProblemDetails from StaffAuthFilter.
POST {{ApiService_HostAddress}}/queue/call-next
X-Staff-Key: {{staffKey}}

###

### Complete a Serving entry (replace {{entryId}} with an id from GET /queue, e.g. the one call-next just
### returned). Returns 404 if the id doesn't exist, 409 if the entry isn't currently Serving. Staff-only, same
### X-Staff-Key requirement as call-next.
@entryId = replace-with-an-entry-id-from-get-queue
POST {{ApiService_HostAddress}}/queue/{{entryId}}/complete
X-Staff-Key: {{staffKey}}

###

### Reconnect catch-up: everything that changed after {{sinceSeq}}. Replace {{sinceSeq}} with a
### sequence number noted from an earlier response (e.g. the one GET /queue returned before you called-next
### or completed anything above). isSnapshot=false + changes=[...] is the common case; isSnapshot=true +
### snapshot={...} means the requested number was unrecognized or too far behind — see
### SqliteQueueRepository.GetChangesSinceAsync for the cutoff. Try 0 to see every change since the seeded data.
@sinceSeq = 0
GET {{ApiService_HostAddress}}/queue/since/{{sinceSeq}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Upload a document against a checked-in entry (public, hardened by allowlist + size cap + the same check-in
### token as POST /checkin — see docs/decisions.md). Replace {{entryId}} above with a real id from GET /queue or
### a check-in response, and {{checkInToken}} with a fresh one from GET /checkin/token (tokens are short-lived;
### reuse the same one across nearby requests, but re-fetch if this 401s).
### Allowed content types: application/pdf, image/jpeg, image/png; 10 MB cap. Wrong type or oversized returns
### 400 with ProblemDetails; unknown entry id returns 404. The referenced file is committed sample data (a
### synthetic intake form, no real court data) under SampleDocuments/.
POST {{ApiService_HostAddress}}/checkin/{{entryId}}/documents
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----DemoBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
X-CheckIn-Token: {{checkInToken}}

------DemoBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample-intake-form.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./SampleDocuments/sample-intake-form.pdf
------DemoBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

###

### List documents uploaded for an entry. Staff-only, same X-Staff-Key requirement as call-next/complete.
### Returns 404 for an unknown entry id.
GET {{ApiService_HostAddress}}/queue/{{entryId}}/documents
Accept: application/json
X-Staff-Key: {{staffKey}}

###

### Stream a single document's content back (replace {{docId}} with an id from the list response above).
### Staff-only, same X-Staff-Key requirement. Returns 404 for an unknown entry or document id.
@docId = replace-with-a-document-id-from-the-list-response
GET {{ApiService_HostAddress}}/queue/{{entryId}}/documents/{{docId}}
X-Staff-Key: {{staffKey}}
